    "advancement": {},
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You can redirect a portion of your spellcasting energy into a defensive shield. When you cast an Arcane spell of 1st circle or higher, you can simultaneously weave a protective ward around yourself.</p><p>While the ward is active, you gain the following benefits if you aren’t wearing medium or heavy armor:</p><ul><li><p>You gain a bonus to your armor class (AC) equal to your PB.</p></li><li><p>You have resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage.</p></li></ul><p>The ward lasts for 1 minute, but ends early if you are knocked unconscious or if your turn ends and you haven’t cast an Arcane spell of 1st circle or higher since your last turn. You can also choose to dismiss your ward at any time (no action required by you).</p><p>You can use this feature a number of times equal to your PB, and you regain all uses of it when you finish a long rest.</p>",
